begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation I remarked on how my new bluetooth ear pieces had been giving me difficulty. We then talked about our prior experiences doing the online video chat study - this my was partner's second time and my fourth time.
middle_memory_text: The middle of the conversation was mostly about the areas in which we lived and how life was. We also spoke of our experiences growing up since we were not too far apart in age.
end_memory_text: Towards the end we talked about the situation with Covid-19 and our outlook for the future. We were both cautiously optimistic that we would get through this and hoped that the better side of human nature would take hold.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of the week I should be relatively busy with work and projects around the house. I'm hoping to spend some quality time with my wife and watch something good on tv. I also plan on spending some time chatting with my mother on the phone to see how she is doing.
critical_positive: Being of the same age group (my partner was 54 and I'm 50), it seemed that we had very many similar experiences particularly when growing up. It was pleasant to talk to someone near my age and discuss how things have changed since when we were young. We were both pretty open to talking about ourselves.
critical_negative: There was definitely a gap in our combined knowledge in terms of geographic locations. My partner did not seem to familiar with my area so mentioning certain locations seemed to confuse him a bit. I also admit that my own knowledge of his location and general area of the country is significantly lacking.

begin_memory_text: George shared how he moved from Jersey to Delaware 11 yrs ago. He talked about the low taxes of Delaware. His property taxes are $700 in Delaware compared to 6k in Jersey. He said people from Jersey, NY, and other states are moving to Delaware for all the good benefits it offers.
middle_memory_text: We discussed the how kids are growing up today in isolated pods. They don't have the same freedoms that we had growing up. George is 50 and I am 54. We are concerned how today's kids are going to turn out.
end_memory_text: We talked about the tshirt that I was wearing, "Be a Good Human". I shared with him the kind of reactions I am getting by wearing the shirt. He just loved the shirt and plans to order one right away. He says they should hand out my shirt with masks to help people to be better to each other.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going as the same as he has for months now. I am attempting to find a decent job since I have a disability. I am interested in the senate hearings for the supreme court nominee. I like the law and wish I would have taken a path in that direction when I was younger.
critical_positive:
George and I are basically the same age, him 50 and me 54. We had very similar experiences growing up and how we are grateful that we grew up the way we did. 
George was a good listener and he liked to share. He wasn't fearful of sharing. I think we respected each other as well.
critical_negative: Oh, sorry to report but there was nothing that didn't work well. The conversation moved along great and smoothly. The time went by too quickly. I could have chatted with him for at least another 30 minutes. We had so much in common, it would be nice if we could be friends.
